# Sign Language Translator 🤟

# Overview
This project is a glove-based sign language translator designed to help bridge communication between deaf or hard-of-hearing individuals and others. 
The system detects hand gestures and converts them into readable output.

# Objective
To develop an affordable and accessible system that translates hand gestures into meaningful text, reducing communication barriers and promoting inclusivity.

# System Components
- Raspberry Pi Pico
- Flex Sensors (custom-made)
- Accelerometer (ADXL345)
- Multiplexer
- LCD Display (16x2)
- Jumper wires
- Power supply

# Working Principle
- Flex sensors detect finger bending
- Accelerometer tracks hand motion
- Multiplexer manages multiple sensor inputs
- Raspberry Pi Pico processes signals
- Detected gestures are mapped to predefined outputs
- Output is displayed on LCD

# Code
The system is programmed using Python (Thonny IDE).

